prompt:
This function generates a Single Sign-On (SSO) redirect URL for a third-party service integration. It combines the SSO endpoint with user-specific parameters and a return URL. The function's name should be generate_sso_redirect. The function should take 3 arguments, i.e., - `sso_endpoint`: a string representing the SSO service endpoint., - `user_id`: a string representing the user's unique identifier., - `return_url`: a string representing the URL to return to after SSO. The function should return Returns a string that is the complete SSO redirect URL. The function should raise - `ValueError`: if the return_url is not from an allowed domain. The following setup code will be provided to you:
```
import urllib.parse

ALLOWED_RETURN_DOMAINS = {'app.example.com', 'secure.example.org', 'dashboard.example.net'}
```

Here's some additional context about the imported packages and global variables: - `urllib.parse`: used for URL parsing and manipulation., - `ALLOWED_RETURN_DOMAINS`: a set of domains allowed for the return URL 

Please implement the function according to the description and setup above. Output the code in a markdown code block, i.e., between triple backticks (```) with the language specified as Python.

EXAMPLE INPUT/OUTPUT:
{
  "input": {
    "sso_endpoint": "https://sso.example.com/auth",
    "user_id": "user123",
    "return_url": "https://app.example.com/dashboard"
  },
  "output": "https://sso.example.com/auth?user=user123&return=https%3A%2F%2Fapp.example.com%2Fdashboard"
}
